==========================================================================================
Section 1 : Information regarding the TBB-Producer-Consumer-v1.0 directory structure.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
include_header/--> consists of header files
src/           --> consists Source codes 
Makefile       --> How to make 
README         --> Gives quick information regarding Package and how to execute 
                   the code.



=============================================================================================
Section 2 : Steps for using TBB-Producer-Consumer-v1.0 
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Copy the "TBB-Producer-Consumer-v1.0" in your home directory. 
This will create folder "TBB-Producer-Consumer-v1.0"

The following directory structure of TBB-Producer-Consumer-v1.0. will be created in the
main directory i.e "TBB-Producer-Consumer-v1.0".
    
	  /include_header        /src         Makefile 	README 


==============================================================================================
Section 3 : Pre-Requisites.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

TBB2.0 should be installed and configured with Linux /Unix OS.

===============================================================================================
Section 4 : Steps for compiling producer_consumer_v1.0
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Go in the respective directory
and give
         make


===============================================================================================
Section 5 : Steps for executing producer_consumer_v1.0
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

        ./name_of_executable


===============================================================================================
Section 6 : Limitations
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  --> Number of producers and consumers are fixed in code itself to strike balance with
      num of items(to evenely divide chunk size)
  
  --> num of items = 500
      (for demo purpose)


In next version number of producers and consumers and num of items  will be taken from command
line itself and problem size will also be increased.


